Set Up an Omnichannel Inventory Connection

Ingest your Omnichannel Inventory data into Data Cloud using the Omnichannel Inventory connector.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To connect to Omnichannel Inventory:	Data Cloud Admin permission set OR Commerce Intelligence Admin permission set
NOTE It’s recommended to connect only one Data Cloud org to one OCI tenant. Connecting more than one Data Cloud org to a single OCI tenant results in unexpected behavior.
From Data Cloud Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Omnichannel Inventory Connector, and then select Omnichannel Inventory Connector.
In the Omnichannel Inventory Connector setup screen, click Connect.
Next to the type of connection that you want to make, click Connect.
Log in to the Omnichannel Inventory instance.
Allow Data Cloud to connect to Omnichannel Inventory and access the data.
Review the connection details.

The connection process creates data streams and maps the data source objects to the data model objects (DMO) and establishes the DMO relationships. If the new connection is in an inactive status for longer than two minutes, navigate to the Data Streams workspace and check if the Omnichannel Inventory data streams are in an error state. If so, click Retry on those streams. If the retry fails, delete the data streams, navigate back to the Omnichannel Inventory Connector setup screen, and create a new connection.

Disconnect an Omnichannel Inventory Connection
You can delete a connection to Omnichannel Inventory if you don’t need it. Removing the connection stops Data Cloud from using your inventory as a data source and data action target.
